    {
      "key": "eb0124b3-2a4c-4b4d-a5eb-66f56e38d7b8",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code. Prompt students to share what they discovered about the following aspects:\n- String concatenation\n- Printing Booleans\n- Arithmetic operators (*, +, -, x, ÷) ",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "Students who successfully complete these levels will have demonstrated mastery of the following lesson objectives:\n- Classify data into fundamental types: strings, integers, floats, and Booleans.\n- Create and modify variables in Python to store and update different types of data.\n- Use operations (e.g., arithmetic, concatenation) to update the values of variables."
          }
        ]
      },
